VIP Smartsearch

X
  • VIP Smartsearch is a framework that supports search within VIP reference documents using query in natural language. It facilitates reordering of search results and keeps record of userâ€™s decision for the ordering of result display and applies that in search of same query on subsequent usage.

  • How to download VIP smartsearch?

    1. Get VIP Smartsearch (Available as a seperate run file).
    2. Set environment variable 
      DESIGNWARE_HOME
      to required designware home location where VIP Smartsearch should be downloaded.
    3. Run 
      vip_smartsearch_<version>.run
      file.
      VIP Smartsearch will be downloaded to the location 
      $DESIGNWARE_HOME/vip/svt/vip_smartsearch/<version>

  • How to install VIP Smartsearch?

    Please refer to the file 
    VIP_Smartsearch_installation_and_usage_guide.pdf
    in 
    $DESIGNWARE_HOME/vip/svt/vip_smartsearch/<version>
    for installation steps.

  • Customer Support

    For more details about VIP smartsearch tool, contact support_center@synopsys.com.
    Mention your queries along with below details and send email to above email id.

    Sub Product: <vip_title>

AMBA AXI_ACE forward_cmos_to_slave_check Monitor check that cache maintenance transactions are forwarded to slaves if forward_cmos_to_slaves_check_enable is set in the slave configuration Checks that cache maintenance transactions are forwarded to slaves If two or more slaves are in the same address space of the memory map, this check is performed on each of the slave ports with overlapping address. When cache maintenance transactions are forwarded to slaves if forward_cmos_to_slaves_check_enable is set in the slave configuration When cache maintenance transactions are not forwarded to slaves if forward_cmos_to_slaves_check_enable is set in the slave configuration
  • The check is performed only if forward_cmos_to_slaves_check_enable is set in the port configuration of the slave

AMBA AXI3 write_byte_count_match_across_interconnect Monitor check that the effective number of bytes bytes for which strobe is asserted of write transactions sent by masters match the effective number of bytes for write transactions sent by interconnect to slave Checks that the effective number of bytes for write transactions sent by master components match that which are sent by the interconnect to the slaves. This basically checks for spurious writes from the interconnect. The effective write byte count is the number of bytes for which write strobe is asserted. If there are writes generated by the interconnect because dirty data returned by a snoop could not be passed back to a master, the effective write byte count includes the number of bytes in a snoop also. ERROR svt_axi_system_checker

AMBA AXI_ACE data_integrity_with_outstanding_coherent_write_check AMBA AXI and ACE Protocol Specification ARM IHI 0022H.c ID012621: Section D6.5.1 Interconnect read from main memory or peripheral device Monitor Check that data returned in a coherent read transaction matches that of a WRITEBACK/WRITECLEAN transaction that was in progress when the read was initiated Checks that the read data returned for a coherent read is the same as that of a WRITEBACK or WRITECLEAN transaction which was in progress when the read was initiated. This is to check that an interconnect that does speculative reads re-fetches the data in a scenario where the preceding WRITEBACK/WRITECLEAN did not complete and none of the snoops returned data. For example, consider that a WRITEBACK was in progress while a read is initiated by the master. If the interconnect does speculative reads, the speculative read may return stale data since the WRITEBACK is not complete. If none of the snoops return data as well, the interconnect should re-fetch data after the completion of the WRITEBACK. When data returned in a coherent read transaction matches that of a WRITEBACK/WRITECLEAN transaction that was in progress when the read was initiated When data returned in a coherent read transaction is not matches that of a WRITEBACK/WRITECLEAN transaction that was in progress when the read was initiated This check is applicable only when:
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: posted_write_xacts_enable is not set.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI_ACE slave_read_xact_timing_relative_to_last_posted_write_xact_check Monitor Check that a read transaction is routed to the slave only after the last posted write transaction with overlapping address from the same port has completed at the slave Checks that a READ transaction is routed to a slave only after a previous WRITE transaction from the same port and with an overlapping address completes at the slave. This is required in posted writes to ensure that a READ transaction retreives the same data as the previous WRITE transaction. When read transaction is routed to the slave only after the last posted write transaction with overlapping address from the same port has completed at the slave When read transaction is not routed to the slave only after the last posted write transaction with overlapping address from the same port has completed at the slave This check is applicable only when:
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: posted_write_xacts_enable is set.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI3 master_slave_xact_data_integrity_check Monitor Check that data in slave transaction matches that in the master transaction Checks that the data in a slave transaction is the same as that of the corresponding master transaction. In order to perform this check, slave transactions are correlated to corresponding master transactions. When only the former is set, this check is done only on non-modifiable transactions. Note that posted_write_xacts_enable can be set only when there are no svt_axi_port_configuration :: AXI_ACE ports in the system. svt_axi_system_configuration :: master_slave_xact_data_integrity_check_enable may be set in systems with ACE components. When data in slave transaction matches that in the master transaction When data in slave transaction is not matches that in the master transaction This check is done only when either of
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: master_slave_non_modifiable_xact_checks_enable,
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: posted_write_xacts_enable or svt_axi_system_configuration :: master_slave_xact_data_integrity_check_enable is set.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI3 data_integrity_check Monitor Check that data is fetched and routed correctly by the interconnect Checks that data in transaction is consistent with data in memory when the transaction completes. This checks that a WRITE transaction issued by a master is written to memory correctly. Similarly, it checks that a READ transaction fetches the correct data from memory. The check assumes that a transaction issued by a master completes only after response is received from the slave to which that transaction was routed. It also assums that there is no other transaction that accesses an overlapping address during the period that the response is issed by the slave and the transaction completes in the master that issued the transaction. In ACE, this check is issued only when the snoop has not returned any data and data is fetched from memory or when data is written to memory. When data is fetched and routed correctly by the interconnect When data is not fetched and routed correctly by the interconnect This check is applicable only when:
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: posted_write_xacts_enable is not set.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI3 slave_transaction_routing_check Monitor Check that transaction is routed to the correct slave based on address Checks that a transaction is routed correctly to a slave port based on address When transaction is routed correctly to a slave port based on address When transaction is not routed correctly to a slave port based on address ERROR svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI_ACE cacheline_and_memory_coherency_check_per_xact Monitor Check that if cachelines of all masters of a particular address are clean, the data in cache should be consistent with data in memory. This check may not pass if a transaction to the slave is in the interconnect's buffer by the time a coherent transaction completes. Checks that if all cachelines are clean, the data in cacheline is consistent with data in memory. This check is done on a per transaction basis at the end of each coherent transaction. Note that in some implementations a transaction to the memory could still be in the interconnect's buffer in which case this check would fail. Hence this check is issued as a warning, rather than an error. When cachelines of all masters of a particular address are clean, the data in cache should be consistent with data in memory This check may not pass if a transaction to the slave is in the interconnect's buffer by the time a coherent transaction completes This check is not performed if the agents connected to the interfaces are configured to work in passive mode. . WARNING svt_axi_system_checker
AMBA AXI_ACE interconnect_generated_write_xact_to_update_main_memory_check Monitor Check that if a snoop response has the PassDirty response asserted, and the interconnect does not assert the PassDirty transaction response for the initiating master, the interconnect must generate a write transaction to update main memory. Checks that the interconnect generated slave write transaction to update main memory when: 1) A snoop response has the PassDirty response asserted, and the interconnect does not assert the PassDirty transaction response for the initiating master 2) The interconnect has provided a read response to an initiating master before it has received all the snoop responses and a later snoop response has PassDirty asserted

This check passes when the system monitor associates interconnect generated slave write transaction to the corresponding snoop transaction that returned dirty data.

This check reports an ERROR at the end of simulation, if the interconnect fails to generate slave write transaction under the above described situations.
  • The master_slave_xact_data_integrity_check must be enabled for this check to function correctly.
  • svt_axi_system_configuration :: interconnect_generated_write_xact_to_update_main_memory_check_enable must to set to 1 to enable this check.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker

  • This check is not performed if the agents connected to the interfaces are configured to work in passive mode.
ERROR svt_axi_system_checker

  • When ACADDR[11:10] is 2'b00 & ACADDR[9:8] is 2'b00 & ACADDR[6] is 1'b0 & ACADDR[5] is 1'b0 then
  • ACADDR[0] is 1'b0

  • ACADDR[0] is 1'b0

  • ACADDR[0] is 1'b1

  • When svt_axi_port_configuration :: check_valid_data_bytes_only_enable=1, it considers only valid byte lanes of wdata based on wstrb
  • When svt_axi_port_configuration :: check_valid_data_bytes_only_enable=0, whole wdata as seen on the bus will be considered
